<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-574-158  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 574 158.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  August 28 1989 v6 n34 p57(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IRMAprint2 bridge links AppleTalk LaserWriters, IBM mainframeprinters. (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Digital Communications Associates Inc. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    DCA.andO;Product:   IRMAprint 2 Bridge for AppleTalk (Computer network software)(product introduction)AppleTalk (Local area network) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionCommunications SoftwareMicro-Mainframe Communication.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Digital Communications Associates Inc. (DCA) recently announcedprotocol-conversion software designed to let Apple LaserWriter printerscommunicate with IBM mainframe printers.andM;IRMAprint2 Bridge for AppleTalk allows LaserWriters on an AppleTalk networkto download mainframe graphics and text, off-loading printing tasks frommainframe printers to the less expensive LaserWriters, according to PeterCheung, vice president and general manager of DCA's Macintosh CommunicationsDivision in Alpharetta, Ga.andM;&quot;This adds value to an existing investment in Apple LaserWriters,&quot; Cheungsaid.andM;The new software resides in the company's existing IRMAprint2 protocolconverter, which currently lets PC-LAN printers communicate with mainframes.andM;Later this year, DCA plans to ship a new version of IRMAprint2 that will letMac users emulate IBM's new Intelligent Printer Data Stream (IPDS), IBM'sSystems Application Architecture (SAA) host-to-printer protocol for printingintegrated mainframe text and graphics onto PostScript-compatible PCprinters, Cheung said.andM;Supporting the Mac 512Ke, Mac Plus, Mac SE and Mac SE/30, IRMAprint2 Bridgefor AppleTalk will be available this fall bundled free of charge with DCA'sIRMAprint2 protocol converter.andP;  The IRMAprint2 costs $1,795.andM;DCA can be contacted at (404) 442-4000.andO;</TEXT>